// chunk c3 negative: a fixed-array global with a count-mismatched ArrayLit
// initializer is a sema ERROR. The ArrayLit path checks the declared count
// exactly (reuse of c2's ArrayLit type-check), so `i64[3] = [1, 2]` errors at
// "array literal for i64[3] needs 3 elements, got 2". Keeps an aggregate-global
// negative case for coverage after the blanket "unsupported in v1" rejection
// was removed (replaced by typed acceptance + initializer validation).
global arr : i64[3] = [1, 2];
fn main() -> i64 { return 0; }
